				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-621562#post-1797721</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-621562/scp-1735#post-1797721</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 16 Jun 2013 18:24:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>SRegan</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1386518</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Sand Castles, Plastic (bags)? :) My assumption would simply be that it's a static phenomenon permeable at times to the sort of plastic used in grocery bags rather than being emanated by the original bag. A nice low-key skip in any case.</p> <p>Actually, I think I may have found a slight discrepancy:</p> <p>&quot;The barrier is spherical, and extends 0.70 meters in all directions around the bag&quot; suggests the barrier moves with the bag, or that the bag is fixed.</p> <p>&quot;The bag appears to approach the edge of SCP-1735 at times, but never seems to exit.&quot; seems to indicate the barrier is static but the bag is blowing around within it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
