					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I remember the fear I had when reading 106 for the first time, and the fridge horror that he might pop up from my ceiling.</p> <p>I remember the thrill that went through me when I read 093, coming late to an appointment how the story and images grabbed me.</p> <p>I remember the squick I had when read 231, when I didn't even realize that my face was wrinkled with disgust as I read it.</p> <p>But they are nothing like this one. I would also recommend making a grain of sand that is of a color unlike the other grains. Because it's anomalooous!</p> <p>-1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
