					<![CDATA[
						 <p>What's so hard to understand? It's a variably permeable force field on a beach. It used to contain sand, but then it became permeable to sand and the sand fell out the bottom.</p> <p>Also, on at least two occasions, it's been unidirectionally permeable to plastic grocery bags. And it's permeable enough to air that the grocery bags are affected by the wind (but remain within the force field).</p> 
